What is the purpose of the `z_importviewingkey` command in Verus?

The `z_importviewingkey` command is used to import a viewing key. Its purpose is not specified, but it is related to `z_exportviewingkey`, which reveals the viewing key corresponding to a given zaddr.

z_exportviewingkey "zaddr"

Reveals the viewing key corresponding to 'zaddr'.
Then the z_importviewingkey can be used with this output

Arguments:
1. "zaddr"  (string, required) The zaddr for the viewing key

Result:
"vkey"         (string) The viewing key

Examples:
> verus z_exportviewingkey "myaddress"
> curl --user myusername --data-binary '{"jsonrpc": "1.0", "id":"curltest", "method": "z_exportviewingkey", "params": ["myaddress"] }' -H 'content-type: text/plain;' http://127.0.0.1:27486/
Can I use `z_exportviewingkey` to export the private key of a zaddr?
No, `z_exportviewingkey` does not export the private key of a zaddr. It reveals the viewing key corresponding to the zaddr. The viewing key is not the same as the private key.

z_exportviewingkey "zaddr"

Reveals the viewing key corresponding to 'zaddr'.
Then the z_importviewingkey can be used with this output

Arguments:
1. "zaddr"  (string, required) The zaddr for the viewing key

Result:
"vkey"         (string) The viewing key

Examples:
> verus z_exportviewingkey "myaddress"
> curl --user myusername --data-binary '{"jsonrpc": "1.0", "id":"curltest", "method": "z_exportviewingkey", "params": ["myaddress"] }' -H 'content-type: text/plain;' http://127.0.0.1:27486/
What is the default value of the "vkey" parameter in the `z_exportviewingkey` command?

There is no "vkey" parameter in the `z_exportviewingkey` command. The "vkey" is the output of the command, which is the viewing key corresponding to the input zaddr. The input parameter is "zaddr", which is the zaddr for which you want to reveal the viewing key.

z_exportviewingkey "zaddr"

Reveals the viewing key corresponding to 'zaddr'.
Then the z_importviewingkey can be used with this output

Arguments:
1. "zaddr"  (string, required) The zaddr for the viewing key

Result:
"vkey"         (string) The viewing key

Examples:
> verus z_exportviewingkey "myaddress"
> curl --user myusername --data-binary '{"jsonrpc": "1.0", "id":"curltest", "method": "z_exportviewingkey", "params": ["myaddress"] }' -H 'content-type: text/plain;' http://127.0.0.1:27486/
